            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I’m a parent of a PSBB student, and based on my experience, I would advise caution before choosing this school.\nMany teachers come across as rude and lack respect toward both parents and students. There appears to be favoritism toward certain groups, while others are not treated equally. The management attitude is also not very approachable.\nThough a few teachers are genuinely good, they are in the minority. There also seems to be yearly filtering of students, with preference given to select groups and top performers, likely to maintain the school’s public image. Unfortunately, my child is not happy going to this school. Sharing this to help other parents make an informed decision.",
